  "target_response": {
    "text": "I'd restructure it in two stages rather than one jump. All I can see from your log is manually entered sleep, about 7.1 hours last night; with no heart-rate, recovery, or workout-history data, I can't verify how you're absorbing your current three days, so the plan itself has to carry the safety margin. Stage one: add a single easy session, keeping your three existing days unchanged, and hold that for a few weeks. If sleep stays steady and you're not carrying soreness into workouts, stage two adds the fifth day, again easy at first. Make the added days low-intensity and different in kind from your hard ones, walking, cycling, or mobility work. Doubling volume in one step is where new aches usually come from; the gradual version gets you to five days nearly as fast with far less risk.",
